The paper deals with game theoretic models of norm diffusion and investigates the robustness of results under adversarial scheduling models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with learning in games, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the diffusion of norms, which is a topic in Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper uses mathematical analysis to investigate the robustness of results, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories.
